For an overview of authentication, authorization and security technologies in Windows, see
  https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/windows/desktop/ee663293(v=vs.85).aspx


Glossary:
Authentication: Verifying the credentials to determine who the user is.
Authorization: Granting or denying the user access to the resource according to a set of rules (and configuration of said rules).
Audit: Logging certain operations (mostly authorization and object access).
